Ukrainian troops attacked the drilling platforms of Chornomorneftegaz at about 8am on Monday morning, the head of Crimea, Sergei Aksyonov, said in a video message on Telegram. Mr Aksyonov said he was in touch with the Russian Ministry of Defence and the FSB in a desperate bid to rescue the workers. There were 12 people on the platforms when it was hit, five were rescued, three were injured and the search for the rest continues. The Ministry of Defence is reportedly leading the rescue operation, with patrol boats and aircraft participating in it. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...